 elaborating on their use of divination, symbolic interpretation of physical features and dress, and interpretations of historical events. As we learn how these ancient people read the world, we begin to see how ancient people found meaning in unexpected ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aJewish art and symbolism. 0aJewish legends. 0aJewish mythology. 0aJudaismxHistoryyPost-exilic period, 586 B.C.-210 A.D. 0aSemioticsxReligious aspectsxJudaism. 0aSymbolism in rabbinical literature. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081474093440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814723784423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814723784/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK